headlines.description: — Joel Embiid returned from his latest injury to score 41 points and grab 10 rebounds and lead the Philadelphia 76ers to a 124-115 victory over the Houston Rockets on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid scores 41 points in return from knee injury. He leads 76ers past Rockets 124-115

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving is the common denominator in the two games with two 40-point scorers in the history of the Dallas Mavericks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kyrie Irving scores 42 and Tim Hardaway Jr. has 41 as Mavs rally past Pelicans 125-120

events.name: Orlando Magic at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — The Orlando Magic are getting bodies back on the bench. So many of them that Paolo Banchero got an extended rest watching them in the fourth quarter.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic rally for 98-94 victory over the Knicks to snap a three-game losing streak

headlines.description: — The Detroit Pistons have done some historic losing this season, including an NBA record-tying 28-game skid. The team’s effort and enthusiasm, however, haven’t wavered.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alec Burks comes off bench and scored 34 points to lead Pistons past the Wizards 129-117

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Trae Young sank his first six 3-point attempts to spark Atlanta's hot-shooting start and the Hawks overcame Victor Wembanyama's big second half to beat the San Antonio Spurs 109-99 on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trae Young starts strong, scores 36 points as Hawks beat Wembanyama-led Spurs, 109-99

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Vince Williams Jr. scored 24, GG Jackson added a career-high 23 points and the Memphis Grizzlies defeated the Golden State Warriors 116-107 on Monday night in <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Vince Williams scores 24 and GG Jackson adds 23 as Grizzlies defeat Warriors 116-107

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 34 points, Jarrett Allen had 10 points and 14 rebounds for his ninth straight double-double, and the Cleveland Cavaliers pulled away late for a 109-91 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Donovan Mitchell scores 34 points as the Cavaliers pull away late to beat the Bulls 109-91

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler returned after missing seven games with a sprained toe and scored 31 points, including two free throws with 11.8 seconds left in overtime to help the Miami Heat beat the Brooklyn Nets 96-95 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores 31 points in return, including two late free throws in OT as Heat beat Nets 96-95

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 19 points and 14 rebounds, Jrue Holiday scored eight of his season-high 22 points in the fourth quarter, and the Boston Celtics won their eighth straight meeting with Toronto, beating the Raptors 105-96 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum has 19 points, 14 rebounds, Celtics win 105-96 for 8th straight over Raptors

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen had 32 points and 10 rebounds, Collin Sexton scored a season-high 30 and the Utah Jazz routed the Indiana Pacers 132-105 on Monday night for their sixth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen and Sexton lead streaking Jazz past banged-up Pacers 132-105 for 6th straight win

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis had 27 points and 15 rebounds, LeBron James scored 25 and the Los Angeles Lakers snapped the Oklahoma City Thunder's four-game winning streak with a 112-105 victory Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James, Anthony Davis lead the Lakers to a 112-105 win over the Oklahoma City Thunder
